  "body": "<!--\r\nNeed help?\r\nRefer to our contributing guidelines for additional information about making a good issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\r\nMany users will not read our docs and try to send transactions with hardcoded gasLimits - e.g. a gasLimit of, 5,000,000 - We must explicitly reject this transactions at the RPC level with a clear error message \r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\nIf the decoded L2GasLimit is 0, return an error message that should read `Invalid transaction: Last 4 digits of tx.gasLimit (5,000,000) decodes to an L2 gas limit of 0 - To read up on how to set your tx.gasLimit, see: [LINK]`\r\n\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nRelated: https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/issues/1062\r\n",
